channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: BREAKING: Israeli Ground Forces Enter Lebanon
NRA targets Sen Sherrod Brown in 7-figure ad buy in Ohio: 'Vote like your life depends on it'
item.description: The National Rifle Association Political Victory Fund is ramping up its influence in swing state Ohio with a new seven-figure ad campaign aimed at Democrat Sen. Sherrod Brown.

item.title: IDF Minister: Israel, U.S. Agree on Need to Dismantle Hezbollah
item.description: Israel and the United States agree on the importance of dismantling Hezbollah's "attack infrastructure" along the Israel-Lebanon border, Israeli Defence Minister Yoav Gallant said on X on Tuesday after speaking to U.S. Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin overnight....

item.title: Dominion and Georgia Face Heat in Court
Montana GOP Senate candidate Sheehy says he was in Afghanistan while Jon Tester was 'eating lobbyist steak'
item.description: Montana GOP U.S. Senate candidate Tim Sheehy criticized his opponent, incumbent Democrat Sen. Jon Tester, for his ties to lobbyists during a debate.

item.title: Rep. Comer to Newsmax: Whistleblower Exposed Walz's CCP Ties
item.description: A whistleblower has come forward to the House Oversight Committee regarding information about Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz's connection to the Chinese Communist Party, Rep. James Comer, R-Ky., told Newsmax on Monday.

item.title: Americans Coming Together: The Silver Lining in a Hurricane's Cloud
Pennsylvania absentee voting underway in some counties
item.description: Mail ballots are available in some of Pennsylvania's 67 counties. The state's 19 Electoral College votes are considered critical for candidates running for president in 2024.

item.title: House GOP Subpoenas HHS Chief Over Missing Migrant Kids
item.description: House Homeland Security Committee Chairman Mark Green, R-Tenn., issued a subpoena to Health and Human Services Secretary Xavier Becerra regarding the whereabouts of tens of thousands of unaccompanied minor migrant children who are in the United States.

item.title: Pete Rose, 'Hit King' and All-Star Cincinnati Reds Player and Manager, Dead at 83
Heightened 'significance and importance' as Vance, Walz face off in VP debate
item.description: With a 2nd face-to-face showdown between Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Trump unlikely, there's a lot on the line in the vice presidential debate with five weeks until Election Day

item.title: Peter Doocy Corners KJP on Troubling Criminal ICE Data, Her Answer Doesn't Go Well
Jimmy Carter becomes first president to turn 100
item.description: Former Democrat President Carter became the oldest president to ever live, celebrating his 100th birthday on Tuesday.

item.title: Harris, Trump Shift Plans After Hurricane Helene's Destruction
